description:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Job Title: &lt;em&gt;Project Manager, Transformation&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Duration: 37.5 hours a week Permanent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employing Organisation: Arden &amp; GEM Commissioning Support Unit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Department: Transformation Warwick office or Derby office (currently working from home due to the pandemic to be discussed during the interview)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary: &lt;em&gt;£45,753 - £51,668&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pay Band: 8a&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Job Type: Permanent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pay Scheme: Agenda for Change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff Group: Admin &amp; Clerical&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Arden &amp; GEM Commissioning Support Unit is an established organisation providing support for a range of health and care customers including Clinical Commissioning Groups, health providers and Local Authorities to help them realise their vision for improving health and health services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working within the Transformation team this role will be responsible for the successful delivery of defined projects to secure improvements to care services and clinical pathways. The successful candidate will be able to demonstrate knowledge of how health systems work, particularly the interdependency of health and social care systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Transformation team operates within an internal framework of supervision and works with other teams in the CSU in a matrix way to deliver seamless services to our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a talented redesign project manager who is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solutions focused&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understands and can apply redesign methodology including change management tools and approaches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work closely with patients and the public to understand needs and help create new models of care and services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptable to new ways of working within an evolving environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer focused and committed to delivering an excellence service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work within a robust project methodology framework&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to demonstrate experience of change management particularly within the health and social care sector&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work flexibly with a range of clinicians and stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, you will have an opportunity to help shape a changing and ambitious organisation that will support you in your development, career needs and aspirations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please refer to the Job description and the Person Specification for details of the role and the skills, qualifications and experience required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion, please email; agcsu.transformation@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBusiness Support Team - Transformation &amp; ConsultancyJob titleProgramme ManagersEmail addressagcsu.transformation@nhs.netTelephone numberby emailAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion about the post of Project Manager please email the Transformation mail box . A member of the Business Support Team will contact you to arrange a convenient time for a telephone discussion.&lt;/p&gt;
